      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver under version control with documented release testing; configuration management records available.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 used under institutional licence with version-controlled case files stored in Git repository. Release notes and solver regression test suite reviewed. Achieved level 2 exceeds MRL 2 requirement of level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions or equivalent demonstrates correct numerical implementation; observed order of accuracy within 10% of theoretical.",
      "rationale": "MMS applied to incompressible Navier-Stokes solver; observed order 1.94 against theoretical 2.0 (3% deviation). Criterion satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI < 5% for primary QoI (NIH) across all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI computed for three-level mesh refinement study. Maximum GCI 3.4% for wall shear stress (primary hemolysis driver); all values below 5% threshold. Medium mesh (3.1M cells) adopted for production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (fluid viscosity, temperature, rotational speed, flow rate) documented and match nominal simulation boundary conditions within stated measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "FDA bench test conditions reproduced from Morrison et al. (2016). Fluid properties (bovine blood analogue, 37°C, viscosity 3.5 mPa·s) and operating points (2000–3500 RPM, 2–6 L/min) documented. Simulation boundary conditions set to nominal published values. No characterisation of test-to-test variability introduced by operator setup was performed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted NIH within ±20% of experimental NIH at all five operating points; RH < 1 at worst-case point.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute percentage error 11.4% across five operating points; worst-case RH = 0.96. Both criteria satisfied. Comparison performed on model outputs generated from correctly specified inputs only."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "NIH and RH index directly map to clinical hemolysis endpoint; QoI traceability to COU decision documented.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the regulatory-accepted metric for pump-induced hemolysis (FDA guidance 2017). RH < 1 acceptance criterion directly supports the COU decision of identifying worst-case operating conditions relative to predicate device. QoI traceability matrix documented in modelling report MR-2024-001."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities performed on the same pump geometry class and operating regime as the COU; fluid and flow conditions within COU envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under CPB-representative flow conditions (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). COU operating envelope fully covered by validation dataset. Geometry fidelity confirmed by independent CAD comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated; residuals below 1e-5 for all transport equations at all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Continuity residual below 1e-6, momentum and turbulence residuals below 1e-5 at convergence for all five operating points. Mass imbalance below 0.01%. Criterion satisfied at required level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Use-error modes associated with clinician or perfusionist interaction with CPB pump settings that could produce off-nominal operating conditions outside the validated envelope are identified and their effect on model predictions characterised.",
      "rationale": "Use-error evaluation is addressed per IEC 62366 in a companion human factors document. No linked artefact, use-error mode taxonomy, or simulation sensitivity study covering operator-induced input deviations (e.g., incorrect flow rate setting, speed ramp profile errors, or priming volume miscalculation by the perfusionist) is included in this credibility package. All validation activities assumed correctly specified nominal inputs. The gap between the companion document reference and this package means that human-error-driven off-nominal conditions remain uncharacterised within the V&V 40 evidence base."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis power-law correlation selection justified by comparison with experimental data and literature precedent.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega selected following sensitivity study against realizable k-epsilon; 6.2% NIH deviation within acceptable range. Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis correlation adopted per FDA guidance and validated against published bench data. Model form uncertainty quantified at ±8% NIH."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sensitivity of NIH prediction to key model inputs (viscosity, inlet velocity profile, rotational speed) quantified; dominant inputs identified.",
      "rationale": "One-at-a-time sensitivity study performed across ±10% variation in inlet flow rate, blood viscosity, and rotational speed. Rotational speed identified as dominant input (NIH sensitivity coefficient 0.74). Viscosity second (0.31). Inlet velocity profile shape had negligible effect (<1%). All sensitivity runs used analyst-prescribed nominal perturbations; no operator misentry scenarios were included in the sensitivity design."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation dataset covers at least three independent operating points spanning the COU flow-speed envelope.",
      "rationale": "Five operating points used for validation, spanning full COU envelope (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). All five points from published FDA experimental dataset (Morrison et al. 2016), providing independent experimental evidence. Minimum requirement of three points satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation boundary conditions demonstrably equivalent to experimental test conditions within measurement uncertainty bands.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rates matched to within 0.05 L/min of experimental set points; rotational speed matched to within 5 RPM. Fluid temperature controlled to 37±0.5°C in experiment; simulation used constant 37°C. Equivalency confirmed within measurement uncertainty. No assessment of equivalency degradation under operator-induced condition deviations was performed."
    }
  ],
